 deadlines and budgets. Responsibilities Perform research on various course topics to ensure content created adheres to the latest national guidelines and evidence-based research. Evaluate source content (gained either from research or handoff from client) to scope courses for delivery via the Amplifire learning platform. Organize course topics into a topic outline that follows a logical structure and includes learning objectives and competencies. Develop, copyedit, and fact check online/digital content based on information from source materials, topic outline, subject matter experts, previous training courses, etc. Define and align courses with client business objectives. Follow project standards and approved styles. Insert images from existing graphic libraries and create custom graphics as needed. Assure the quality of content output through self-checks, peer reviews and functional testing. Build and maintain strong client relationships. Light project management by creating project schedules and adhering to internal timelines, client deadlines, budget, and delivery deadlines. Work under pressure to deliver quality content on deadline. Carry out other duties as assigned. Qualifications Required: Bachelor\u2019s degree in English, Communications, Journalism, Education, Instructional Design, or similar At least 3 years of formal writing experience Experience partnering with external client stakeholders, SMEs, and other parties in the development of learning programs Proven superior writing skills, including the ability to write concise, creative, and effective instruction, especially for online learning Excellent proofreading and editing skills Exceptional verbal communication skills Proficiency in leading/facilitating virtual meetings with clients and colleagues. Strong conceptualization and design abilities for the production of animation, graphics, video, and print materials Attention to detail and scientific accuracy Ability to multi-task and prioritize tasks related to project timelines Open collaborative style with the ability to work with remote team members Proficiency in MS Office applications Preferred Experience working in healthcare, medical device, pharma, or related industry Experience (in instructional design, technical writing, editorial or related) in production environment Experience writing instructional content Experience writing graphic requests, audio/video scripts for production Experience with Captivate, Camtasia, Storyline or other eLearning Authoring Experience with learning analytics Note: Please be prepared to provide a cover letter and samples of any prior work that demonstrates your skills and ability to deliver on the needed job responsibilities. To apply for this position, please email your resume and cover letter. Show full job description Quick Apply Stay Connected Contact Us SimplyHired Blog Facebook Twitter LinkedIn YouTube Job Tools Local Jobs Salary Estimator Post Jobs Free Resume Builder Browse All Jobs All Salaries All Cities All Companies Guides Resumes Cover Letters Interviews Careers Take your job search wherever you go. United States United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center |Â Do Not Sell My Personal Information"
